comments.body:
[~vasya], [~tsugawa], [~lbiasi], [~gholms]:

I have the tests on VPCMIDO working, planning to test EDGE now.  Successful VPC test here:

http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint_4.4/50/

Changes to selinux package are here:

https://github.com/mbacchi/eucalyptus-selinux/commits/dev-mbacchi-EUCA-12424

Oddly there are still some selinux errors but the regression test above was successful.  They are(on the CLC):


{code:java}
[root@b-34 ~]# audit2allow -a


#============= eucalyptus_cloud_t ==============
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t user_home_dir_t:dir search;

#============= eucalyptus_eucanetd_t ==============
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t cgroup_t:dir { open read search };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t cgroup_t:file { getattr open read };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t init_t:file { getattr open read };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t init_t:lnk_file read;

#!!!! The file '/run/systemd/private' is mislabeled on your system.  
#!!!! Fix with $ restorecon -R -v /run/systemd/private
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t init_t:unix_stream_socket connectto;
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t self:capability sys_resource;
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t self:process setrlimit;
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t syslogd_var_run_t:dir read;
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t syslogd_var_run_t:file { getattr open read };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t systemd_systemctl_exec_t:file { execute execute_no_trans open read };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t systemd_unit_file_t:service { start status };
allow eucalyptus_eucanetd_t tmpfs_t:filesystem getattr;
{code}

I will discuss with [~gholms] today and determine if they need correcting with additional policy changes or can be left for now.
